        <animation property="pos" to="0.22 0.5" begin="2000" duration="1000" mode="linear"/>
      </storyboard>
    </image>
    <image name="background" extra="true">
      <zIndex>90</zIndex>
      <storyboard>
        <animation property="pos" to="1.5 0.5" begin="0" duration="0" mode="linear"/>
        <animation property="pos" to="0.95 0.5" begin="2000" duration="1000" mode="linear"/>
      </storyboard>
    </image>
    <video name="videocrton" extra="true">
      <path>./../../_inc/anim/video/CRT_ON.mp4</path>
      <delay>0</delay>
      <loops>0</loops>
      <effect>none</effect>
      <origin>0.5 0.5</origin>
      <pos>0.48 0.4</pos>
      <maxSize>0.22</maxSize>
      <zIndex>26</zIndex>
    </video>
    <video name="videobox" extra="true">
      <path>{random}</path>
      <path>./../../_inc/anim/video/${system.theme}.mp4</path>
      <!-- Loads platform video from addon directory, if available -->
      <path>./../../../ckau-book-addons/_inc/anim/video/${system.theme}.mp4</path>
      <default>./../../_inc/anim/video/CRT_Noise.mp4</default>
      <delay>0</delay>
      <effect>none</effect>
      <origin>0.5 0.5</origin>
      <origin if="${screen.ratio} == '4/3'">0.52 0.49</origin>
      <pos>0.48 0.4</pos>
      <maxSize>0.22</maxSize>
      <zIndex>25</zIndex>
      <storyboard>
        <animation property="pos" to="0.20 0.4" begin="2000" duration="1000" mode="linear"/>
      </storyboard>
    </video>
    <text name="TextDate" extra="true">
      <pos>0.49 0.2</pos>
      <text>1978</text>
      <fontPath>./../../_inc/fonts/ubuntu_condensed.ttf</fontPath>
      <color>666666</color>
      <fontSize>0.025</fontSize>
      <zIndex>140</zIndex>
      <storyboard>
        <animation property="y" from="0.1" begin="3000" duration="1000" mode="linear"/>
        <animation property="opacity" to="0" begin="0" duration="0" mode="linear"/>
        <animation property="opacity" from="0" to="1" begin="3000" duration="1000" mode="EaseIn"/>
      </storyboard>
    </text>
    <text name="TextManufacturer" extra="true">
      <pos>0.49 0.255</pos>
      <text>APF Electronics</text>
      <fontPath>./../../_inc/fonts/ubuntu_condensed.ttf</fontPath>
      <color>FFFFFF</color>
      <fontSize>0.04</fontSize>
      <zIndex>140</zIndex>
      <storyboard>
        <animation property="x" from="0.5" begin="3000" duration="1000" mode="linear"/>
        <animation property="opacity" to="0" begin="0" duration="0" mode="linear"/>
        <animation property="opacity" from="0" to="1" begin="3000" duration="1000" mode="EaseIn"/>
      </storyboard>
    </text>
    <text name="TextName" extra="true">
      <pos>0.49 0.30</pos>
      <size>0.5 0</size>
      <text>M-1000</text>
      <fontPath>./../../_inc/fonts/ubuntu_condensed.ttf</fontPath>
      <color>FFFFFF</color>
      <fontSize>0.065</fontSize>
      <lineSpacing>1.1</lineSpacing>
      <zIndex>140</zIndex>
      <storyboard>
        <animation property="x" from="0.5" begin="3000" duration="1000" mode="linear"/>
        <animation property="opacity" to="0" begin="0" duration="0" mode="linear"/>
        <animation property="opacity" from="0" to="1" begin="3000" duration="1000" mode="EaseIn"/>
      </storyboard>
    </text>
    <text name="TextDesc" extra="true">
      <size>0.5 0</size>
      <pos>0.49 0.4</pos>
      <text>The APF Microcomputer System is a second generation 8-bit cartridge-based home video game console released in October 1978 by APF Electronics Inc. with six cartridges. The console is often referred to M-1000 or MP-1000, which are the two model numbers of the console. The APF-MP1000 comes built-in with the game Rocket Patrol. The APF-MP1000 is a part of the APF Imagination Machine.

It is the successor to the APF TV Fun line of first generation consoles.</text>
      <text lang="pl">APF Microcomputer System to 8-bitowa domowa konsola do gier wideo drugiej generacji, wydana w październiku 1978 roku przez APF Electronics Inc. z sześcioma kartridżami. Konsola jest często określana jako M-1000 lub MP-1000, które są dwoma numerami modelu konsoli. Do konsoli APF-MP1000 dołączona jest gra Rocket Patrol. APF-MP1000 jest częścią APF Imagination Machine.

Jest następcą linii konsol APF TV Fun pierwszej generacji.</text>
      <text lang="ru">Игровая приставка второго поколения, представляет собой 8-битную домашнюю игровую приставку.

Является преемником линейки консолей APF TV Fun, относящихся к первому поколению. Выпущена в октябре 1978 компанией APF Electronics Inc. с шестью игровыми картриджами. Устройство упоминается как M-1000 или MP-1000, поскольку это номера модели консоли.</text>
      <text lang="it">L'APF Microcomputer System è una console per videogiochi domestici a 8 bit di seconda generazione, rilasciata nell'ottobre 1978 da APF Electronics Inc. con sei cartucce. La console viene spesso indicata come M-1000 o MP-1000, che sono i due numeri di modello della console. L'APF-MP1000 veniva fornito con il gioco Rocket Patrol. L'APF-MP1000 fa parte della APF Imagination Machine.

È il successore della linea di console APF TV Fun di prima generazione.</text>
      <fontPath>./../../_inc/fonts/ubuntu_condensed.ttf</fontPath>
      <color>666666</color>
      <fontSize>0.025</fontSize>
      <lineSpacing>1.1</lineSpacing>
      <zIndex>140</zIndex>
      <storyboard>
        <animation property="y" from="0.8" begin="3000" duration="1000" mode="linear"/>
        <animation property="opacity" to="0" begin="0" duration="0" mode="linear"/>
        <animation property="opacity" from="0" to="1" begin="3000" duration="1000" mode="EaseIn"/>
      </storyboard>
    </text>
  </view>
</theme>
